The Birnin Gwari Emirate Progressives Union (BEPU) on Saturday stated that killings and abductions on Birnin Gwari-Kaduna highway have resumed in full force by armed bandits. Barrister Salisu Haruna, Chairman of BEPU, in a statement sent to DAILY POST, said on Saturday criminals opened fire on some travelers along the highway killing one person and injuring others.
